<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1280">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/22.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Cándido Aguilar to-day sent communication to Huasteca Petroleum
                            Company placing company war tax at $100,000. Complete copy this second
                            demand being forwarded by mail. As yet have received no answer to letter
                            sent to General Aguilar but copy issued was read to-day over telephone
                            to his representative at Juan Casiano when he presented these second
                            demands.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>